<statement><div><p>The radius of a circle is <alert><m>{22.4}</m> cm</alert>. The circle is enlarged by a scale factor of <alert><m>{0.25}</m></alert>. Find the circumference of the image of the circle after the enlargement.</p><p><fillin characters="5" name="ans1"/> cm</p></div></statement>
<solution><div><h3>Worked solution</h3>

<p>
The original radius is <m> r = {22.4} </m> cm.
</p>

<p>
After enlargement by a scale factor of <m> {0.25} </m>, the new radius is</p>
<p>
<m>
r' = {0.25} \times {22.4} = {5.6}
</m> cm.
</p>

<p>
The circumference of a circle is given by
<m>
C = 2\pi r.
</m>
</p>

<p>
So the circumference of the enlarged circle is</p>
<p>
<m>
C = 2\times \frac{22}{7} \times {5.6} = {35.2}
</m> cm.
</p>

<p>
Equivalently, since circumference scales linearly,</p><p>
<m>
C = {0.25} \times (2\times \frac{22}{7} \times {22.4}) = {35.2} 
</m> cm.
</p></div></solution>
<answer><p><m>35.2</m></p></answer>
</stack-static>